manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: About Us 20 YEARS OF ADVENTURE At BOB Gear, we believe raising families is a way to discover the world all over again. We’ve spent the last two decades creating revolutionary products that give you the freedom to find adventure together. The mantra we live by? Put quality first and the rest falls into place. This commitment is at the forefront of our innovations. Rugged Beginnings Back in 1994, Roger Malinowski, a bicycle industry maven, met Philip Novotny, an airline mechanic. Together, they brought an innovative bike trailer to the masses. When Roger and Philip began to start families, they were inspired to design and build a jogging stroller that held the same high standards as their trailers. The result was the Sport Utility Stroller. “We wanted the best of a bunch of worlds,” says Roger. “A lightweight, high-quality stroller that you could still take running, hiking or off-road and fold up easily and compactly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Travel Bag Is Awesome
reviews.reviewText: I love this travel bag. It is made perfectly for the BOB stroller. Sure you can buy a cheaper bag but this is sturdy and the price tag of the stroller warrants the bag made for it. I don’t see the point of buying a bag where the stroller can be damaged because it’s ill fitted. The only thing is after having traveled with my infant I’m never bringing this stroller again. It’s easier to just buy a smaller more compact stroller that can fit as a carry-on in the overhead bin. You have to take the wheels off and while this doesn’t take a lot of time it’s not what I want to do before boarding. Don’t think about traveling on a plane alone because it’s way to cumbersome to maneuver and hold a baby. With that said this bag will be used for road-trips.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Big but worth it
reviews.reviewText: We love our Bob stroller so we definitely wanted to take it on our vacations involving airplanes. This bag is very big but it's the only one we could find with wheels and a handle which makes it so much easier to carry opposed to being a backpack! It did require some assembly to put the bag together and the stroller wheels need removed to fit properly in the bag, but it's with it to travel with.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 27, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect yet tight fit for the BOB allterian Pro
reviews.reviewText: We purchased this for an upcoming trip. The Allterain Pro fits snuggly and seems to be well secured. One trick was making sure to pass the strap under the canopy when securing the stroller.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 19, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great travel bag for all strollers
reviews.reviewText: I used this for my Baby Jogger City Select Double stroller and everything fit perfectly. The wheels on the bag made traveling with it easy and the whole bag rolled up and stored nicely once we got home. I highly recommend this for anyone traveling and needs and airplane bag for their stroller.

reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Great until you use it
reviews.reviewText: We were really impressed with the quality of this product, until we went to use it. The first time we tried to use it, which was for a short flight, the bag totally fell apart. The zipper broke, the material thinned in spots. The seams started to fray, etc. For a product as expensive as this one, I am pretty disappointed.
